to Misaka Full Boost.

243
00:11:19,791 --> 00:11:22,166
[gun cocks and fires]

244
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:24,000
[KAMIJO] Seriously?

245
00:11:29,791 --> 00:11:31,416
The underground mall?

246
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:33,208
[YOMIKAWA] We performed a
full analysis of the message

247
00:11:33,291 --> 00:11:34,458
she left on the
answering machine

248
00:11:34,541 --> 00:11:35,750
and we came up
with some frequencies

249
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:37,625
that were pretty distinct.

250
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:39,458
They indicate that
she's in Area U,

251
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:42,291
and that essentially
means the underground mall.

252
00:11:42,375 --> 00:11:44,000
[ACCELERATOR] Fine.
So that's where you're

253
00:11:44,083 --> 00:11:45,041
telling me to go, then?

254
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:46,541
[YOMIKAWA]
That's the plan for now.

255
00:11:48,125 --> 00:11:49,791
But we'll see.
She moves fast on those

256
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:51,291
little legs of hers,
so who knows if

257
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:53,666
she'll be there by
the time you arrive.

258
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,583
[YOMIKAWA] Hey, Accelerator?

259
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:56,833
Yeah, what is it?

260
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,166
[YOMIKAWA] Why are
you so afraid to show

261
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,041
kindness to other people?

262
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:01,250
[ACCELERATOR] Say what?

263
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:02,875
You take it in stride
whenever Last Order

264
00:12:02,958 --> 00:12:04,708
is affectionate
or sweet with you,

265
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,208
but you seem to draw
the line when it comes

266
00:12:06,291 --> 00:12:08,875
to showing her any
kindness on your part.

267
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:11,000
[YOMIKAWA] I think it's because
you're afraid that once you do,

268
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:12,583
there will be no going back.

269
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:14,083
Thanks for the lecture.

270
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:15,708
[YOMIKAWA] I know.
It's not like I can ever

271
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:18,833
completely understand where
you're coming from, is it?

272
00:12:18,916 --> 00:12:20,583
Not with the things
you've been through,

273
00:12:20,666 --> 00:12:22,166
the way you grew up.

274
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:23,541
[ACCELERATOR] Tch.

275
00:12:23,625 --> 00:12:26,416
The old X-S.
The Exceptional Esper

276
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:29,416
Multi-Modification
Technical Research Institute.

277
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:33,125
Home sweet home until
I reached the age of nine.

278
00:12:33,208 --> 00:12:36,916
The place was like a landfill
for disposing of human beings.

279
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,208
You must've heard
the stories, right?

280
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:41,875
[YOMIKAWA] It was my squad
that neutralized the Institute.

281
00:12:41,958 --> 00:12:44,083
I oversaw its dismantling.

282
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:45,333
[ACCELERATOR] Thanks for that.

283
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:46,833
[YOMIKAWA]
I saw it, too, you know.

284
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,000
What they kept hidden away

285
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,208
on the other side
of those heavy doors.

286
00:12:50,291 --> 00:12:52,875
[ACCELERATOR] And just think,
I was such a monster

287
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:55,333
even the X-S Institute
couldn't handle me.

288
00:12:55,416 --> 00:12:57,708
I'm sure Yoshikawa
told you...

289
00:12:57,791 --> 00:13:00,083
about what I did in
those "experiments."

290
00:13:00,166 --> 00:13:03,250
Showing kindness isn't
exactly my strong suit.

291
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:05,333
You were young, they didn't
give you much of a choice.

292
00:13:05,416 --> 00:13:08,125
But you still hate
yourself, even now.

293
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:09,458
There's a rule that I follow.

294
00:13:09,541 --> 00:13:12,583
Not Antiskill's,
but one I made for myself.

295
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:14,750
[YOMIKAWA] I will never
turn a weapon on a child,

296
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:18,791
no matter what. Not even if
that child's a powerful esper.

297
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:20,625
Do you know why that is?

298
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:24,291
[YOMIKAWA] Yeah.
I thought you would.

299
00:13:24,375 --> 00:13:27,541
And, sure, maybe it doesn't
even compare to your situation.

300
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:30,458
But the fact of the matter
is that we're both indebted.

301
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:33,041
You and I, we've got
quite a lot to pay back

302
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:35,583
before we can
hope to rest easily.

303
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:37,416
In some ways, I envy you.

304
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,375
At least you have
power to work with.

305
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:41,916
That gives you more
options than I've got.

306
00:13:43,041 --> 00:13:44,083
[ACCELERATOR]
What if I'd used my power

307
00:13:44,166 --> 00:13:45,833
to stop the experiments?

308
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:47,583
Or found a way to
keep them from rushing

309
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,791
headlong toward
their inevitable deaths?

310
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:53,708
What if even now, after
all this, it's not too late?

311
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,208
[ACCELERATOR] What if...?

312
00:14:00,041 --> 00:14:01,750
This is a buncha crap.

313
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:04,041
[YOMIKAWA] Well, you know, it's
hanging on to that kind of crap

314
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:06,666
that pushes us to
make good on our debts.

315
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,583
Hm.

316
00:14:10,625 --> 00:14:12,333
[ACCELERATOR] Damn it all.

317
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:22,583
[CROWD chatter]

318
00:14:22,666 --> 00:14:24,833
Isn't this what the
report said to look out for?

319
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:25,916
[ANTISKILL B]
It's an impressively made

320
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,458
3D image, all right.

321
00:14:27,541 --> 00:14:29,250
[ANTISKILL A] These pranks get
more convoluted every year,

322
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:31,583
don't they?
Well, let's contact HQ

323
00:14:31,666 --> 00:14:34,791
and get the names of espers
who could pull this off.

324
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:38,041
[KAMIJO] Man, am I beat. What
was that all about, anyway?

325
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:40,208
[MIKOTO] That big, stupid jerk!

326
00:14:40,291 --> 00:14:42,458
[breathing heavy]

327
00:14:42,541 --> 00:14:44,791
Does he think he can
get away with this, huh?

328
00:14:44,875 --> 00:14:47,375
[MIKOTO] What am I,
chopped liver?

329
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:49,458
[gasps and cheering]

330
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:51,791
[breathing heavy]

331
00:14:51,875 --> 00:14:54,666
How is it I always end up
in the middle of these things?

332
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:56,833
Just my luck, I guess.

333
00:14:56,916 --> 00:14:58,333
"Why are you sitting
with your shoulders

334
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:00,416
all slumped like
you're exhausted?"

335
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,583
asks Misaka Misaka.

336
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:04,791
Uh!

337
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:06,000
[LAST ORDER] Stealthily
coming up behind you

338
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:08,125
and giving you a hug
to make you feel better.

339
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:09,583
[KAMIJO] Hey!

340
00:15:11,041 --> 00:15:14,833
The Mini-Misaka from
earlier. Wow you are tiny.

341
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:21,291
♪

342
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:22,250
[thud]

343
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,750
[INDEX groans]

344
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:25,625
I'm so hungry.

345
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:28,125
[ACCELERATOR] Huh?
What do we have here?

346
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:30,041
[stomach growls]

347
00:15:33,416 --> 00:15:35,500
[INDEX] So anyway, I was
out looking for Toma,

348
00:15:35,583 --> 00:15:37,750
but then I got hungry
and I couldn't keep going.

349
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:39,833
You can eat or you
can talk. Pick one.

350
00:15:39,916 --> 00:15:42,291
Well, anyway, when you're
done stuffing your face,

351
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:44,208
I've got a question for you.

352
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:48,375
Sure, you can ask me anything!

353
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:49,833
Man, you're disgusting.

354
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:52,125
Thank you for the food!
My name is Index, by the way.

355
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:53,708
It's nice to meet you!

356
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:56,583
[ACCELERATOR] First, wipe off
your face. Then we can talk.

357
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:02,000
[phone beeping]

358
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:04,375
Here, take a look.

359
00:16:04,458 --> 00:16:06,125
Have you seen this kid
wandering around anywhere?

360
00:16:06,208 --> 00:16:07,125
[INDEX] Nope, sorry.

361
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:08,541
You barely even looked.

362
00:16:08,625 --> 00:16:09,708
But I don't need to.

363
00:16:09,791 --> 00:16:11,875
I never forget the
faces of people I see.

364
00:16:11,958 --> 00:16:13,583
Well, I should
get back out there!

365
00:16:13,666 --> 00:16:15,125
I'll have a much
easier time of it

366
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:17,291
now that my stomach is full.

367
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:19,083
[INDEX] Though, of course,
now that I'm not so hungry,

368
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:22,250
my need to find Toma somehow
doesn't seem quite as pressing.

369
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:23,833
[ACCELERATOR]
Well, nice to meet ya.

370
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:25,583
Hope you find someone
else to help you look.

371
00:16:25,666 --> 00:16:26,708
'Cause I'm not gonna.

372
00:16:26,791 --> 00:16:28,208
[INDEX] Why not? Are you busy?

373
00:16:28,291 --> 00:16:31,708
Yeah. That's it.
I'm incredibly busy.

374
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:34,625
[KAMIJO] So what
you're saying is,

375
00:16:34,708 --> 00:16:36,333
you're essentially
like a host computer,

376
00:16:36,416 --> 00:16:38,416
with all the Misaka
Sisters tied into you?

377
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,958
[LAST ORDER] "Probably more like
a console than a host computer,"

378
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:43,541
says Misaka Misaka,
correcting your statement.

379
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:46,125
"The Misaka Network has
no central point anywhere.

380
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:48,083
So it doesn't really mean
anything for there to be

381
00:16:48,166 --> 00:16:50,833
a specific individual acting
as the Misakas' 'core,'

382
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:53,958
so to speak," says Misaka
Misaka authoritatively,

383
00:16:54,041 --> 00:16:56,041
enjoying the chance
to give a lecture.

384
00:16:56,125 --> 00:16:57,916
[sighs]

385
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,708
"Well, anyway, the
reason I came back was

386
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:01,708
to say thank you for all
the help you gave Misaka

387
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:03,708
when those awful
experiments were going on.

388
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:05,750
Even thinking about
them gives me the shivers,"

389
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,375
says Misaka Misaka,
shivering illustratively.

390
00:17:08,458 --> 00:17:11,208
Sure. What are you
actually doing here?

391
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:13,000
"You don't believe me?
You're such a jerk!"

392
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:15,083
shrieks Misaka Misaka,
stomping her feet to show

393
00:17:15,166 --> 00:17:17,541
just how angry she is.
Then she decides to swing

394
00:17:17,625 --> 00:17:19,625
[LAST ORDER] her fists around
in your face for good measure!

395
00:17:19,708 --> 00:17:22,041
My bad, okay I'm
sorry? Hey, I know.

396
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:23,125
[KAMIJO] If you
promise to forgive me,

397
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,500
I'll buy you some popcorn.

398
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:26,291
"You actually think
offering to buy a girl

399
00:17:26,375 --> 00:17:28,541
a snack will make her forget
that you hurt her feelings?

400
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:31,500
What kind of an idiot
are you?" asks Misaka Misaka,

401
00:17:31,583 --> 00:17:33,833
unable to look at you anymore.

402
00:17:35,416 --> 00:17:36,958
So, like I was saying,
Toma is always

403
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:39,208
running off somewhere,
leaving me behind.

404
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:41,333
He doesn't even give
me an explanation.

405
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:43,458
It's like his feet don't
know how to stay in one place,

406
00:17:43,541 --> 00:17:45,875
[INDEX] he heads out before
he even knows he's going.

407
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,416
[grunts]

408
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,833
Heh. So, why did you want to
come to the underground mall?

409
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:51,166
I'm looking for someone.

410
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,791
The girl in that picture
you showed me, right?

411
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:54,083
Wow. You catch on quick.

412
00:17:54,166 --> 00:17:55,416
I wish I could find
a way to thank you

413
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,750
properly for feeding me.

414
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,708
Here's an idea. How about
you shut up and go away?

415
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:00,833
[INDEX] I really don't
know how I can repay you.

416
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:02,583
I just gave you a
perfect suggestion.

417
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:03,833
Why don't you take it?

418
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:05,791
[INDEX] You're worried
about that girl, huh?

419
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:06,916
[giggles]

420
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,166
Let's work as a team!

421
00:18:08,250 --> 00:18:10,041
I'll help you look
for her until I find Toma.

422
00:18:10,125 --> 00:18:11,333
Huh?

423
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:13,291
[INDEX] 'Kay?

424
00:18:13,375 --> 00:18:15,375
Uh. Damn it all.

425
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:19,583
Ah!

426
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,625
Wanna know something?

427
00:18:21,708 --> 00:18:23,166
"Misaka snatched
these from somebody.

428
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:25,250
Somebody tough!"
says Misaka Misaka,

429
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,375
[LAST ORDER] happily
bragging about her trophy.

430
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:29,958
Oh, really? I'm finally
starting to relax,

431
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:31,083
and now you're
gonna tell me you're

432
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,291
some kind of bandit?

433
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:34,333
Hold on. I recognize those.

434
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:36,125
[KAMIJO] Misaka's sister
was looking for them.

435
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:37,750
"Unfortunately, these
goggles were made to fit

436
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:39,916
a person a lot
bigger than Misaka.

437
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,958
So she can't put
them on to use them.

438
00:18:43,041 --> 00:18:46,125
It's really disappointing,"
says Misaka Misaka regretfully.

439
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:48,708
Hey, uh, you know you
can just shorten the length

440
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,208
of the band, don't you?

441
00:18:50,291 --> 00:18:51,875
[LAST ORDER] Huh?

442
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:58,541
Ahhh!

443
00:18:58,625 --> 00:19:01,000
Uh, are you okay down there?

444
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:02,958
[whimpers]

445
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:04,208
[INDEX] Hm...

446
00:19:04,291 --> 00:19:05,875
You know, I almost
feel like I recognize her

447
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:07,583
from somewhere,
but there's something off,

448
00:19:07,666 --> 00:19:09,500
and I can't put my finger on it.

449
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:11,916
Nope, I have no idea
who she is. I'm sorry.

450
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,750
Then give me my
phone back already!

451
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,541
Ya good for
nothin' little brat.

452
00:19:15,625 --> 00:19:17,541
[growls]

453
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,833
[KAMIJO] There, all done!

454
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:21,000
Ah...!

455
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:23,500
"That's great!
Misaka can see perfectly!"

456
00:19:23,583 --> 00:19:26,250
says Misaka Misaka,
delighted by the change.

457
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,166
"But Misaka remembers
what you said before,

458
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:30,875
and she hasn't forgiven you,"
Misaka Misaka asserts,

459
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:32,625
[LAST ORDER] taking time to
scold you for your rudeness

460
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:35,833
before returning to
her celebratory dance.

461
00:19:35,916 --> 00:19:37,500
Yeah, yeah.

462
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:41,208
"It's almost time. Misaka
can't stay much longer.

463
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:43,833
She has to get going,"
Misaka Misaka says

464
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,750
[LAST ORDER] in a somber tone,
delivering the bad news.

465
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:50,250
Oh, I didn't realize
what time it was.

466
00:19:50,791 --> 00:19:52,500
"It makes me sad.
I wish we could spend

467
00:19:52,583 --> 00:19:55,833
more time together," says
Misaka Misaka, with a sigh.

468
00:19:55,916 --> 00:19:58,041
"Maybe some other
time, though."

469
00:19:58,125 --> 00:20:00,583
"Misaka admits our
encounter was coincidental,

470
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:01,958
but the part about
wanting to thank you

471
00:20:02,041 --> 00:20:04,708
for your help was the
truth," says Misaka Misaka,

472
00:20:04,791 --> 00:20:07,291
hoping you know how
sincerely she means it.

473
00:20:07,375 --> 00:20:08,958
"I really have to
get home soon, though,

474
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,541
or he'll be worried."

475
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:11,791
Who'll be worried?

476
00:20:11,875 --> 00:20:13,250
[LAST ORDER] "If Misaka
stays out too late,

477
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:15,958
he'll probably think he
needs to go look for her."

478
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:19,000
"And Misaka doesn't want to be
an inconvenience or anything.

479
00:20:19,083 --> 00:20:21,833
You know?" asks Misaka
Misaka with a smile.

480
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:25,083
[KAMIJO] Well, sounds like this
friend of yours is a nice guy.

481
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:28,791
"He's had a hard time.

482
00:20:28,875 --> 00:20:31,291
He was hurt physically,
mentally, and emotionally.

483
00:20:31,375 --> 00:20:34,333
It may be too much for
one person to heal from.

484
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:36,250
He wants to be strong,
but Misaka knows that

